-- India's universal healthcare rollout to cost $26 billion: official
-- By Aditya Kalra
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 05:41AM EDT
-- None



NEW DELHI, Oct 30 (Reuters) - India's universal health plan that aims to offer guaranteed benefits to a sixth of the world's population will cost an estimated 1.6 trillion rupees ($26 billion) over the next four years, a senior health ministry official said.

Under the National Health Assurance Mission, Prime Minister Narendra Modi's government would provide all citizens with free drugs and diagnostic treatment, as well as insurance cover to treat serious ailments.